---
description: development and automoation workflows
globs: ["*.py", "*.js", "*.ts", "*.sh"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Use this workflow for new tasks:

1. Open VS Code in the relevant project directory
2. Install dependencies (npm install, pip install, etc.)
3. Run the local development server if applicable
4. Open the project in the browser on localhost
5. Verify logs and outputs before continuing

- Always check for existing environments before creating new ones
- Format code before saving
- Standardize naming conventions for branches and files